                        "displayName": "Neal Richardson",
                        "active": true,
                        "timeZone": "America/Los_Angeles"
                    },
                    "body": "Yeah I get that, but we seem to be able to print 1.4 as \"1.4\" and not \"1.400000001\", so we have some way of determining that.\r\n\r\n{code}\r\n> Scalar$create(1.4)\r\nScalar\r\n1.4\r\n> Scalar$create(1.4)$type\r\nFloat64\r\ndouble\r\n{code}",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/user?username=npr",
                        "name": "npr",
                        "key": "npr",
                        "avatarUrls": {
                            "48x48": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?avatarId=34045",
                            "24x24": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=small&avatarId=34045",
